[30;1m199 | [0m[35m- The behavior of the config file expansion ``%(here)s`` has changed.  In[0m
[30;1m200 | [0m[35m  previous versions, a bug caused ``%(here)s`` to always expand to the[0m
[30;1m201 | [0m[35m  directory of the root config file.  Now, when ``%(here)s`` is used inside[0m
[30;1m202 | [0m[35m  a file included via ``[include]``, it will expand to the directory of[0m
[30;1m203 | [0m[35m  that file.  Thanks to Alex Eftimie and Zoltan Toth-Czifra for the patches.[0m

[30;1m205 | [0m[35m- The default value for the config file setting ``exitcodes=``, the expected[0m

[30;1m197 | [0m[35m- The ``supervisor`` package is no longer a namespace package.[0m
[30;1m198 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m199 | [0m[35m- The behavior of the config file expansion ``%(here)s`` has changed.  In[0m
[30;1m200 | [0m[35m  previous versions, a bug caused ``%(here)s`` to always expand to the[0m
[30;1m201 | [0m[35m  directory of the root config file.  Now, when ``%(here)s`` is used inside[0m
[30;1m202 | [0m[35m  a file included via ``[include]``, it will expand to the directory of[0m
[30;1m203 | [0m[35m  that file.  Thanks to Alex Eftimie and Zoltan Toth-Czifra for the patches.[0m

[30;1m4 | [0m[35mOverview[0m
[30;1m5 | [0m[35m--------[0m
[30;1m6 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m7 | [0m[35mSupervisor is a client/server system that allows its users to control[0m
[30;1m8 | [0m[35ma number of processes on UNIX-like operating systems.  It was inspired[0m
[30;1m9 | [0m[35mby the following:[0m
[30;1m10 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m11 | [0m[35mConvenience[0m

[30;1m28 | [0m[35m"""Basic infrastructure for asynchronous socket service clients and servers.[0m
[30;1m29 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m30 | [0m[35mThere are only two ways to have a program on a single processor do "more[0m
[30;1m31 | [0m[35mthan one thing at a time".  Multi-threaded programming is the simplest and[0m
[30;1m32 | [0m[35mmost popular way to do it, but there is another very different technique,[0m
[30;1m33 | [0m[35mthat lets you have nearly all the advantages of multi-threading, without[0m
